    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix type confusion in ngap_gNB_get_instance function signature\n\n### Summary\nThere's a type mismatch between the declaration and definition of `ngap_gNB_get_instance` function that can cause incorrect behavior when retrieving gNB instances. The header file declares the parameter as `uint8_t mod_id` while the implementation uses `instance_t instance`, leading to potential type confusion issues.\n\nThis inconsistency can cause problems when the function is called with an `instance_t` parameter but the declaration suggests it expects a `uint8_t`. The calling code consistently passes `instance_t` parameters, so the implementation is correct but the declaration needs to be updated to match.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_management_procedures.h`: Updated function declaration to use `instance_t instance` parameter to match implementation and added necessary include for platform_types.h\n- The function signature now correctly matches between declaration and definition\n\n"
}